    {
      "title": "NC DIT’s FirstTech Annual Review 2020",
      "elements": [
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Executive Summary",
          "id": "heading-1"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "North Carolina Department of Information Technology’s First Responder Emerging Technologies (FirstTech) program worked to support first responders throughout the state during 2020. This year presented an opportunity to pivot the program to virtual platforms as the COVID-19 pandemic impacted the entire nation. FirstTech was able to still strive in meeting our program goals in 2020 and continues to provide tremendous value to the responders in North Carolina as well as participating in national efforts. FirstTech continued to manage the federal State/Local Implementation Grant Program 2.0 (SLIGP 2.0) and provided valuable programs with the federal money while meeting match requirements using in-kind contributions rather than state funds. While travel restrictions effectively ended the FirstTech Travel Scholarship Program of SLIGP 2.0, work continued on the data-sharing workshops which were delivered using virtual platforms. FirstTech staff was able to support various agencies during planned and unplanned events and disasters, bringing knowledge of advanced technologies to support first responder missions. This annual review is presented to leadership to highlight accomplishments of the prior calendar year.",
              "bold": false,
              "italic": false,
              "underline": false,
              "strikethrough": false,
              "superscript": false,
              "subscript": false,
              "code": false
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Vision",
          "id": "heading-2"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "To create a North Carolina where all responders can seamlessly and securely communicate using advanced technologies.",
              "bold": false,
              "italic": false,
              "underline": false,
              "strikethrough": false,
              "superscript": false,
              "subscript": false,
              "code": false
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Mission",
          "id": "heading-3"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "To serve North Carolina’s responder community through thought leadership, direct experience, and unbiased information to support responders’ understanding, adoption, and usage of the best technologies available.",
              "bold": false,
              "italic": false,
              "underline": false,
              "strikethrough": false,
              "superscript": false,
              "subscript": false,
              "code": false
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Accomplishments",
          "id": "heading-4"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "The following list is to highlight the work that was accomplished in 2020 and is in no particular order. Several of these items are on-going and more details can be provided upon request.",
              "bold": false,
              "italic": false,
              "underline": false,
              "strikethrough": false,
              "superscript": false,
              "subscript": false,
              "code": false
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Responder Engagements",
          "id": "heading-5"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "list_type": "unordered",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Laird was voted to serve as the Vice Chair of the State Interoperability Executive Committee (SIEC)",
                  "bold": false,
                  "italic": false,
                  "underline": false,
                  "strikethrough": false,
                  "superscript": false,
                  "subscript": false,
                  "code": false
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Grasso represents the greater Broadband Infrastructure Office on the SIEC",
                  "bold": false,
                  "italic": false,
                  "underline": false,
                  "strikethrough": false,
                  "superscript": false,
                  "subscript": false,
                  "code": false
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Participation in the SIEC included planning update for the Statewide Communications Interoperability Plan (SCIP), update to the required VIPER template, chairing a working group to establish best practices for new collaboration applications being used",
                  "bold": false,
                  "italic": false,
                  "underline": false,
                  "strikethrough": false,
                  "superscript": false,
                  "subscript": false,
                  "code": false
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Continued participation on NC 9-1-1 Board Technology Committee",
                  "bold": false,
                  "italic": false,
                  "underline": false,
                  "strikethrough": false,
                  "superscript": false,
                  "subscript": false,
                  "code": false
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Established a limited lending library for some of the latest first responder communication devices",
                  "bold": false,
                  "italic": false,
                  "underline": false,
                  "strikethrough": false,
                  "superscript": false,
                  "subscript": false,
                  "code": false
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Assisted City of Charlotte IT with coverage testing for cellular provider evaluation",
                  "bold": false,
                  "italic": false,
                  "underline": false,
                  "strikethrough": false,
                  "superscript": false,
                  "subscript": false,
                  "code": false
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Currently assisting NC Office of State Fire Marshal with evaluation of two-way radio replacements",
                  "bold": false,
                  "italic": false,
                  "underline": false,
                  "strikethrough": false,
                  "superscript": false,
                  "subscript": false,
                  "code": false
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Assisted NC State Highway Patrol with evaluation of collaboration application",
                  "bold": false,
                  "italic": false,
                  "underline": false,
                  "strikethrough": false,
                  "superscript": false,
                  "subscript": false,
                  "code": false
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "2020.03.10 Facilitated connection with Durham County and FirstNet AT&T to provide support during a ransomware attack that affected Durham City & County governments.",
                  "bold": false,
                  "italic": false,
                  "underline": false,
                  "strikethrough": false,
                  "superscript": false,
                  "subscript": false,
                  "code": false
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "2020.08.03 Provided pilot of Bridge platform in support of hurricane response. Feedback was overwhelming positive and may lead to a change in communications during incidents.",
                  "bold": false,
                  "italic": false,
                  "underline": false,
                  "strikethrough": false,
                  "superscript": false,
                  "subscript": false,
                  "code": false
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "On-going assistance to North Carolina National Guard Aviation unit with radio programming and technologies",
                  "bold": false,
                  "italic": false,
                  "underline": false,
                  "strikethrough": false,
                  "superscript": false,
                  "subscript": false,
                  "code": false
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Dual-sim and embedded SIM (eSIM) testing on a smartphone which led to discussions with NC Emergency Management on the pros and cons as well as feedback for the wireless carriers on what worked and what didn’t.",
                  "bold": false,
                  "italic": false,
                  "underline": false,
                  "strikethrough": false,
                  "superscript": false,
                  "subscript": false,
                  "code": false
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
